Introduction

This is a radar-based technology that detects and recognizes birds, reducing the risk of bird strikes and potential threats from bird-like aircraft, to ensure the safety of airplanes

Recently, bird strikes have occurred frequently, and bird-like aircraft such as bionic flapping wing planes pose a potential threat to the national security. Radar has the functions of radio detection and distance measurement. Using radar to identify bird targets can reduce the occurrence of events above.
